
** Control Files

  - Control files describes the physical structure of the
    database. Each time the physical structure changes, the control
    files should be backuped.

  - The database name.
  - The timestamp of database creation.
  - The names and locations of the associated datafiles and redo log
    files.
  - Tablespace information.
  - Datafile offline ranges.
  - The log history.
  - Archived log information.
  - Backup set and backup piece information.
  - Datafile copy information.
  - The current log sequence number.
  - Checkpoint information.


